  title: Log message
- message: Note that there are multiple numpy/scipy functions that do regression,
    fitting, etc. Of these, scipy.stats.linregress fits a line and forces an intercept.
    You do not have to explicitly add 1s or anything. numpy.linalg.lstsq does plain
    old linear regression - your inputs can even be matrices. It simply returns argmin
    |ax - b|^2 for given a and b, and therefore does not force an intercept. The last
    one I want to mention is scipy.optimize.leastsq. This one is a non-linear least
    squares solver, and I know nothing more about it.
  tags:
