  title: Log message
- message: To make vim display italicised text, see [this](http://www.nerdyweekly.com/posts/enable-italic-text-vim-tmux-gnome-terminal/)
    wonderful blog entry. Essentially, we need to manually map the escape sequences
    to the keywords `sitm` and `ritm`, which are used by vim to set and remove italic
    mode respectively. The file in question, `xterm-256color-italic.terminfo`, has
    been added to the `misc` repository as well. It contains all relevant install
    info. Note that `TERM` must be set to `xterm-256color-italic` by `gnome-terminal`
    for this to take effect. [This](http://askubuntu.com/questions/233280/gnome-terminal-reports-term-to-be-xterm)
    askubuntu question tells you how to do it. Set the command executed by `gnome-terminal`
    to be `env TERM=xterm-256color-italic /bin/bash`.
