- message: 'I ran into issues with Numpy+MKL again when I upgraded numpy. `pip3 install
    --upgrade numpy` does not respect `~/.numpy-site.cfg` once again. This is probably
    because pip just installs binaries, instead of running `setup.py` and compiling
    from source. You have to force a recompilation by using `pip3 install --no-binary
    :all: numpy` in order to make it work. If needed, throw in a `--ignore-installed`
    as well. Refer [this](https://stackoverflow.com/a/41984963/525169) SO answer.'
