- message: 'To better visualize the call tree after profiling a python script, first
    save your output from cProfile using `python -m cProfile -o <myscript.profile>
    <myscript.py>`. You will need to install [`pyprof2calltree`](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyprof2calltree/)
    via pip and `kcachegrind` via apt. Then, visualize the profile data with `pyprof2calltree
    -i <myscript.profile> -k`. Reference: [this](https://stackoverflow.com/a/3561512/525169)
    SO answer.'
