- message: 'It is really easy to step into debug mode in a python script. Simply add
    `import pdb; pdb.set_trace()` at any point in your script and you will have effectively
    created a breakpoint. Your script will slide into a debugging session with a python
    prompt. Watch out though: there are several single-letter commands which will
    override your variable names. For instance, `b` stands for break or something
    like that, so if you have a variable called `b`, you will not be able to inspect
    it. Use `exec("print(b)")` in all such cases, to side-step this issue.'
  tags:
